Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.76,0:00:25.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Translated to En by: Spimer and Ned\NTimed and Typesetted by: Ned
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.83,0:02:28.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The Gathering of the Detectives\N(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.53,0:02:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My rental car is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.19,0:02:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My Ferrari is being burned too
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.94,0:02:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My Alfa Romeo and the old man's\NOogami's Porsche are burning too
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.73,0:02:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all this, I guess my car\Nat the rear has also burnt up
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.78,0:03:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the rear...? You didn't\Npark your car here, Ms. Maid?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.11,0:03:03.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.12,0:03:06.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master told me to\Npark it by the back door
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.53,0:03:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! It's safe
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.72,0:03:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't this seem strange to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.49,0:03:24.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit must've forgotten\Nto rig a bomb in this car
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.85,0:03:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go check whether the bridge\Nhas really been destroyed or not
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.51,0:03:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm coming
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.84,0:03:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall come along as well
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.44,0:03:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm in, too
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.94,0:03:36.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, there... Too many\Npeople will sink the boat
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.98,0:03:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about we decide who\Ngets to go with coins?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.86,0:03:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I happen to have five coins
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.26,0:03:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, kid! You're thoughtful
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.20,0:03:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a primitive method, but
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:57.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it can't be helped
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.90,0:04:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those who get heads on their coins
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.45,0:04:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will go to the bridge with the car
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.47,0:04:14.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be careful, dad
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.86,0:04:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.90,0:04:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.04,0:04:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.32,0:04:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa! What a hideous sight
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bridge's been completely destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.32,0:04:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Granny Senma
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.65,0:04:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please switch the headlights to\Nshort range! I can't see the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.55,0:04:46.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, let's see... Short range, short range...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.77,0:05:08.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ms. Senma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.40,0:05:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ms. Senma!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.76,0:05:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ehh? Ms. Senma was killed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.51,0:05:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... It seems that the car was altered\Nso it'll explode if you touched the lights
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.48,0:05:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we keep waiting, we'll be killed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.13,0:05:31.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's split up and search if there's really\Nsomeone else besides us in the mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:35.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then... us women will make a team of 3
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.60,0:05:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way we can go to the bathroom together
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.23,0:05:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the brown-haired\Nand fair-skinned boy at?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.43,0:05:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No idea
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.49,0:05:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he's feeding the\Nhawk he brought along
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.77,0:05:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.04,0:05:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stylish stuff we've got here
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.57,0:06:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are brand new scratching\Ntraces on the piano's edge
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.82,0:06:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are probably scratch\Nmarks made by a hawk
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.89,0:06:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means that that boy\Ncame by to check this room
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.65,0:06:15.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le! Something's stuck\Nbetween the piano keys
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.36,0:06:18.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.37,0:06:23.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the Luminol solution\Nthat the miss brought with her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.47,0:06:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she's also come here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.44,0:06:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Whiskers! Turn off the lights!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.39,0:06:30.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.47,0:06:42.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Karasuma will kill despite\Nthat I finally got the trump\Ncard to solve the cipher
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.22,0:06:52.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where's the maid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.63,0:06:57.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she'd wait on the corridor outside\Nthe restroom, will you go check it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.72,0:06:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.20,0:07:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ms. Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.32,0:07:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The maid!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.07,0:07:26.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.24,0:07:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit who rigged the car with a bomb\Nwouldn't ride on it and risk themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.30,0:07:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit must be one of us who stayed in\Nthe mansion... You, me, Ms. Ran, and the maid
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh my, boy... Aren't you\Ncarrying a dangerous toy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.78,0:07:51.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was beneath the bed's\Nmattress in my room
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.79,0:07:55.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You intended to place the\Nblame on me afterwards, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.66,0:07:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh my, what a coincidence
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:08:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was thinking the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.69,0:08:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had the same deduction as you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:10.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A gunfire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.51,0:08:20.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No good
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.89,0:08:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His heart's been pierced
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.00,0:08:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.56,0:08:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stairs
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.40,0:08:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's climbing the stairs
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:33.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This rascal!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.77,0:08:37.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A PC?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.34,0:08:42.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ms. Souda!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.13,0:08:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.59,0:08:49.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's set up so that a needle pops\Nout if you turn the inner knob
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.67,0:08:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoever inputted the\Ntreasure's location in the PC
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.08,0:08:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,would be poisoned when they\Ntried to leave the room
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.09,0:09:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, where's the culprit at?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.54,0:09:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.81,0:09:10.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way she'd fall for her own trap
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.25,0:09:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And your daughter and the maid\Nare napping in the restroom
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.31,0:09:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that gunfire was fake
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.24,0:09:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,only you or I could've killed them
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.10,0:09:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if it wasn't me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.22,0:09:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it has to be you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.35,0:09:40.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Translated to En by: Spimer and Ned\NTimed and Typesetted by: Ned
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.51,0:09:44.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmpf, I like to eliminate\Ntrouble at its earliest stage
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.10,0:09:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't hate me,\NMr. Sleeping Kogorou
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.17,0:10:05.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.91,0:10:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the greatest\Ndetectives couldn't solve it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.25,0:10:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hidden cameras footage is cut off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.92,0:10:30.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.52,0:10:40.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,"I've solved the treasure's cipher.\NI want to tell you it in person.\NCome to the dining room. I'm the 7th deective."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.19,0:10:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.67,0:10:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the detectives I invited should\Nbe dead! There can't be a 7th detective
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.93,0:11:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally, you wouldn't think that someone who rigs a bomb in a\Ncar would ride in that car, unless they wanted to commit suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.13,0:11:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's an exception
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.30,0:11:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when they want to use the explosion as camouflage,\Nso it looks like they've died in the explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.51,0:11:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.13,0:11:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Senma
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.93,0:11:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, you secretly came out of the\Ncar before it exploded and hid
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.51,0:11:28.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How silly... I noticed the\Nbomb in the last second
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.75,0:11:33.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,escaped the explosion and\Njust made my way back here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:39.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, didn't we decide who'd\Nride the car by flipping coins?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.28,0:11:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew you'd ride in the\Ncar even before flipping them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.57,0:11:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you had a coin on your left\Nhand's palm surface from the start
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.47,0:11:53.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You hid it by placing your right hand, with\Nanother coin on it, on top of the left hand
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.31,0:11:57.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You pretended to catch the flipped coin,\Nbut you actually let it fall to the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.18,0:12:00.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then revealed the one\Nyou were already holding
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.85,0:12:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so that you'd always get heads
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.47,0:12:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had a ten yen coin on you when\Nyou checked Mr. Oogami's black tea
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.24,0:12:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so wasn't it easy for you? Ms.\N"phantom of the child abandoned by God"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.45,0:12:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Are you saying I'm the organizer\Nof the banquet and Mr. Oogami's killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.53,0:12:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me, then
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:26.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did I manage to make just\NMr. Oogami drink potassium cyanide?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.16,0:12:31.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And how could I predict when he'd do so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.12,0:12:34.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His black tea had no poison in it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.05,0:12:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Mr. Mouri was between our seats
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.30,0:12:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sitting order doesn't matter
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.72,0:12:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you had coated all of the tea\Ncups with potassium cyanide beforehand
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.73,0:12:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You placed it where the\Nhandle and the cup touched
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.30,0:12:57.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Mr. Oogami held the cup, the edge\Nof his right thumb would touch that spot
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.98,0:13:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's also next to his nail, which he\Nunconsciously bit when he was lost in thought
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.50,0:13:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But all of us did wipe clean all of\Nthe cutlery to be on the safe side
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.66,0:13:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.17,0:13:14.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was very careless of Mr. Oogami, who\Nwas such a great and renowned detective
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.28,0:13:19.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if he was your friend and\Nan organizer of this banquet
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.18,0:13:22.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not impossible for him\Nto underestimate the risk
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.55,0:13:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,by thinking he wouldn't get\Nkilled and thus be less on guard
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.31,0:13:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.11,0:13:31.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You killed your accomplice, Mr. Oogami, and\Nthen made it look like someone killed you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.44,0:13:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You invited the detective here to solve the\Ncipher and to psychologically corner them
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.94,0:13:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,have them find the treasure's location\Nand then finally, you'd kill them all
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.25,0:13:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like what the millionaire\NKarasuma Renya did 40 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a name at the end of the\Npiano's bloody text... Senma Kousuke
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.84,0:13:54.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.35,0:13:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the name of my father
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.50,0:14:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was an archaeologist... He was summoned\Nto this Twilight Mansion 40 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.18,0:14:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A millionaire that was over 100 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.43,0:14:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,had found a clue to a treasure hidden in the\Nmanor he'd inherited from his mother in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.85,0:14:17.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And wanted to have a look at it before\Ndying, so he wanted my father to find it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.57,0:14:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seemed like it was a very well-paid job, we received big heaps\Nof money each day along with a daily letter from my father
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.99,0:14:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So both my mother and I were glad
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.52,0:14:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,6 months later, both the money and\Nthe letters suddenly ceased to come
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.70,0:14:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And my father, who hadn't told us\Nwhere he had been, went missing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.91,0:14:42.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got to know the truth of his disappearance when I held the last\Nletter he sent us, which I'd kept as a substitute of him, to the light
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.22,0:14:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were holes in the letter made\Nby a needle... It was a secret message
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.65,0:14:53.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There he narrated about the cipher\Nwhich told the treasure's location
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.61,0:14:56.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that many other scholars apart\Nfrom my father had been summoned there
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:15:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and about how Karasuma, feeling his death looming close,\Nlost his temper and began to kill the scholars one by one
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.33,0:15:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,within the mansion as\Na warning to the others
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.14,0:15:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you tell that to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.23,0:15:15.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No... I didn't discover the text written\Nwith the needle until 20 years after
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.16,0:15:21.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By then Renya had already died, the Karasuma family had\Ndeclined and the mansion had passed to other owners
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.96,0:15:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It all began when I accidentally slipped\Nthis story to Mr. Oogami two years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.70,0:15:34.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He located this mansion at once, went\Nmad and began to search for the treasure
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.19,0:15:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he was unable to solve the cipher
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.34,0:15:41.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had accumulated a huge\Ndebt from buying this mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.74,0:15:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and, one day, when he couldn't\Nwaltz out of things, he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.24,0:15:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Let's gather the detectives\Nand have them solve the cipher!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.89,0:15:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll use Kaitou Kid as bait\Nto lure the detectives in!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.23,0:15:56.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's make him the inviter and set up\Na game in which we stake our lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.19,0:16:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And make it look like, at some point in\Nthe game, that he's killed both of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.17,0:16:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did you kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.32,0:16:12.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I realized that he intended to kill\Nus, including me, once we found the treasure
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.92,0:16:17.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Making it look like we'd shot each\Nother with the guns he put in our rooms
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.10,0:16:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make the detectives continue to solve the cipher, I had no choice\Nbut to stop that man, who behaved like he was possessed by Karasuma
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.54,0:16:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The result is the same as 40 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.01,0:16:34.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cipher hasn't been solved and\Nthe tragedy has repeated itself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.56,0:16:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it seems like your\Nfather did solve the cipher!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.89,0:16:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.25,0:16:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's odd that despite that it's such a huge\Nmansion, the only clock here is this one here in the dining hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.36,0:16:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the beginning of the cipher "On the night\Nthat the two travelers looked up at the skies"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.81,0:16:55.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,means 12 AM, when both of\Nthe clock's hands aim upwards
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.85,0:16:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First step is to return them to 12 AM
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the key to solve the rest of the cipher is the\Ntrump card your father wrote in the bloody text
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.73,0:17:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The trump card... A set of trumps
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.79,0:17:16.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The king, queen and knight in the\Ncipher are the K, Q, and J cards
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.29,0:17:20.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the treasure is diamonds, the holy\Ngrail is hearts, and the sword is spades
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.43,0:17:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We follow the direction of the faces on the cards in the\Nmansion and move the hands from the 12 AM position accordingly
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.59,0:17:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,13 to the left, 12 to the\Nleft, and 11 to the right
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.89,0:17:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The coating has come off,\Nand gold emerges from inside
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.36,0:17:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.70,0:17:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think my father died\Nover such a trivial thing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.80,0:17:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess this is what reality is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.25,0:18:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, Ms. Senma... You promised us
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.77,0:18:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me the way to escape this mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.82,0:18:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was never such a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.58,0:18:09.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I intended to die here
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.95,0:18:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that Mr. Oogami believed me when I told\Nhim I'd secretly explain it to him after dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.97,0:18:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmpf! Thought as much
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.75,0:18:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Granny Senma
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.61,0:18:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh. And this was my best suit
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.29,0:18:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I said this\Nchild's play was pointless
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.50,0:18:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if you have any complaints,\Ntell them to the boy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.22,0:18:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who said that she might\Nreveal the way to escape if it was a kid
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.22,0:18:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You actually pretended to be\Ndead just to make me reveal that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.91,0:18:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did you know I was the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.46,0:18:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since this boy had us choose the coins
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.37,0:18:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stretched your arm and bothered to\Npick the 10 yen coin which was further away
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.10,0:18:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you didn't want anyone else\Nto pick the 10 yen coin
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.81,0:19:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you had touched a 10 yen coin when\Nyour fingers had potassium cyanide on them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:05.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a chemical reaction would've occurred,\Nand the trick would've been found out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.98,0:19:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we narrowed it down to you, thus\Nwe were able to unite our forces
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.38,0:19:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we looked at the body's right hand\Nnail, we saw through the trick you used
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.05,0:19:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.20,0:19:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the issue now is how\Ndo we escape from this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.22,0:19:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.07,0:19:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah. It's probably the sound of\Nthe police helicopter I called for
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.38,0:19:29.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Called?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.58,0:19:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watson must've delivered the letter I\Nput on his anklet to my housekeeper's car
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.87,0:19:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which I had on standby down the cliff
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.18,0:19:41.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Phew... I'm glad I put an X mark on\Nit to tell it apart from other cars
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.73,0:19:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case then you\Nshould've told us earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.98,0:19:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And yet you let us\Nin that monkey show
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.08,0:19:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's not only the helicopter's sound
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.21,0:19:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can hear the sound of something crumbling
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.10,0:19:52.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.67,0:21:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he didn't come in the end, Kaitou Kid
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.88,0:21:19.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Did you want him to come?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.65,0:21:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.23,0:21:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, granny
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.58,0:21:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was old Oogami the one who planned\Nto psychologically corner us, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.09,0:21:30.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you pretended to be\Ndead after you'd killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.02,0:21:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to solve it... Solve the\Ncipher that my father left to me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.27,0:21:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whilst I'm still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.50,0:21:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I thought there wouldn't be another chance like\Nthis one, in which you great detectives would be gathered
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.00,0:21:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the one who was possessed\Nby Karasuma Renya was me after all
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.23,0:21:55.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.73,0:21:59.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.03,0:22:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.21,0:22:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaito Kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.65,0:22:11.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, grandma
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.80,0:22:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you too old to be in a rush to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.03,0:22:16.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't say such nonsense
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.93,0:22:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saved you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.68,0:22:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.65,0:22:23.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To apologize for organizing\Nthis banquet in your name
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.23,0:22:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I didn't do this, you wouldn't have\Nbeen able to run away from those children
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.30,0:22:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially from that small boy who\Nwas aiming at you with his odd watch
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.83,0:22:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! I got seen through, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.07,0:22:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the cigarettes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.34,0:22:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogorou is a heavy smoker
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.05,0:22:43.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You hadn't smoked any since\Nyou came to the mansion, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.76,0:22:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are those children?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.26,0:22:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess they're like the lover that\Nyou don't want to stumble upon!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.90,0:22:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's a pity
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.88,0:22:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You came because you were\Nafter Karasuma's treasure, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.39,0:22:59.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that was my intent\Nbut I've given up on it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.26,0:23:04.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That doesn't fit into a thief's pocket
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.06,0:23:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The walls have crumbled,\Nand there's gold inside
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.43,0:23:16.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that clock was a switch to\Nmake the outer walls crumble, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.29,0:23:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected of Karasuma's mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.72,0:23:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it must be worth a hundred\Nbillion at the least
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.78,0:23:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.25,0:23:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twilight is that time of the\Nevening when the sky glows golden
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.38,0:23:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's indeed a golden mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.59,0:23:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That asides, where's my real dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.50,0:23:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Achoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.07,0:23:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ha, I'm here...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:14.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next episode:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.62,0:23:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about Maria Higashio
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.82,0:23:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Maria's shoes and backpack
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.42,0:23:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's open
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.21,0:23:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bookshelves are fallen
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.14,0:24:02.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a high chance she has been\Nstuck somewhere for more than 6 hours
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.09,0:24:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A phone call from Hattori
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.42,0:24:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hel—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.83,0:24:08.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.05,0:24:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Search for Maria{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}\NPart 1
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.04,0:24:34.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.56,0:24:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cover
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.06,0:24:37.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What happened to the mansion at the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.08,0:24:38.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It had a good luck
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.80,0:24:40.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A word play?
